   225→  // The number of outstanding readDisable to be called with parameter value true.
   226→  // When downstream send buffers get above high watermark before response headers arrive, we
   227→  // increment this counter instead of immediately calling readDisable on upstream stream. This is
   228→  // to avoid the upstream request from being spuriously retried or reset because of upstream
   229→  // timeouts while upstream stream is readDisabled by downstream but the response has actually
   230→  // arrived from upstream. See https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/issues/25901. During the
   231→  // deferring period, if the downstream buffer gets below low watermark, this counter gets
   232→  // decremented. Once the response headers arrive, call readDisable the number of times as the
   233→  // remaining value of this counter.
